free_txt: Analysis of 58Ni data.
58Ni analyzing powers.
58Ni cross sections.
LAMPF.
Corrected for background.
Quadrupole-dipole-dipole spectrometer.
Four scintillators provided pulse-height and time-of-
flight information.
Beam current monitored using
. 2 ionization chambers placed behind target in the
scattering chamber,
. a split secondary-emission monitor monitor down-
stream from the target, and
. 2 four-counter particle telescope arrays located in
the scattering plane at 45 and 135 degrees relative
to the target.
Statistical uncertainty.
LAMPF.
Beam polarization typically 0.87.
Approved by L. Ray, 24 December 1999.
Normalization uncertainty 15 %.
The published data correspond to LAMPF Experiment 311,
cycle 18.  These were supplemented in 1982 with
additional data from cycle 22 of LAMPF Experiment 311.
The latter were never published.  The complete p+54Fe
elastic scattering data at 800 MeV from Exp. 311 are
given here.
